# Frontend — UX/UI standards

Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS in `ygo_app/static/`. Follow existing patterns before inventing new ones.

## Design system

- Use CSS variables from `:root` in `style.css`: `--bg`, `--surface`, `--accent`, `--muted`, `--radius`, etc.
- Reuse existing classes (`.tab`, `.secondary`, `.hidden`, `.filter-group--compact`, modal patterns) before adding one-off styles.
- Keep the dark theme; do not introduce light-only colors without `color-scheme` consideration.

## Accessibility

- Match patterns in `index.html`: `role="tablist"`, `aria-label`, `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls`, `aria-labelledby`.
- Every interactive control needs a visible label or `aria-label`; icon-only buttons must have `aria-label`.
- Preserve keyboard use: focusable elements, logical tab order, `:focus-visible` styles.
- Use semantic HTML (`button` for actions, `label` + `for` for inputs, `main`/`nav`/`section`).

## UX patterns

- **Loading:** immediate feedback — skeleton/shimmer for modals, `#import-progress` for long ops.
- **Empty / error:** user-facing messages, not silent failures; disable actions until data is ready.
- **Responsive:** keep `viewport` meta; use flex/wrap patterns; avoid fixed widths that break on mobile.
- **Destructive actions:** confirm before delete; use `--danger` and existing delete button styling.

## Security & DOM safety

- Insert untrusted API text via `textContent`, not `innerHTML`. Default is text-only; sanitize explicitly if HTML is ever required.

## Project conventions

- After editing CSS or JS, bump the `?v=` query string on the matching `<link>` / `<script>` in `index.html`.
- Prefer `app.js` patterns (event delegation, stale-response guards, tab memory cache) over per-row listeners.

## Examples

```
BAD:  el.innerHTML = card.name
GOOD: el.textContent = card.name

BAD:  New purple button styles ignoring --accent
GOOD: Reuse .secondary / .tab and CSS variables

BAD:  Clickable <div> with no keyboard support
GOOD: <button type="button"> with aria-label if icon-only
```
